<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-017-295 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 453 998</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Nov 4 1991 v8 n44 p85(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Buyers say price, image limit use of TFT portables. (thin-filmtransistor color portable computers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mann, Mary.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Buyers say they like the small size and vivid colors of thin-filmtransistor (TFT) color portable computers, but they agree thatprices for the computers are too high and image quality does notyet compare to that offered by traditional CRT displays.andP;  OneDolch Computer Systems Inc computer user appreciates the compactsize of the portable, while another notes that his Dolch system isuseful for graphical interfaces but would be more useful if itcould be used on battery power.andP;  Toshiba users complain about thehigh price and weight of their systems, and although they find theToshiba displays relatively attractive, the displays do notcompare with color desktop monitors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dolch Computer Systems Inc. (Products)Toshiba America Information Systems Inc. (Products).andO;Topic:     User NeedsPortable computersColorThin-Film Circuits.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Buying concerns: TFT color portables. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>